Create a PHP Admin Login, Logout form using session variables.

CODE:
<?php
session_start();

// Hardcoded admin credentials (demo purpose)
$admin_user = "admin";
$admin_pass = "12345";

// Logout handler
if (isset($_GET['logout'])) {
    session_unset();
    session_destroy();
    header("Location: ".$_SERVER['PHP_SELF']);
    exit();
}

// Login handler
if ($_SERVER["REQUEST_METHOD"] == "POST") {
    $username = $_POST['username'];
    $password = $_POST['password'];

    if ($username === $admin_user && $password === $admin_pass) {
        $_SESSION['admin'] = $username;
        header("Location: ".$_SERVER['PHP_SELF']);
        exit();
    } else {
        $error = "Invalid Username or Password!";
    }
}
?>

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <title>Admin Login System</title>
</head>
<body>
<?php if (isset($_SESSION['admin'])): ?>
    <!-- Admin Dashboard -->
    <h2>Welcome, <?php echo $_SESSION['admin']; ?>!</h2>
    <p>You are now logged in as Admin.</p>
    <a href="?logout=true">Logout</a>
<?php else: ?>
    <!-- Login Form -->
    <h2>Admin Login</h2>
    <?php if (!empty($error)) echo "<p style='color:red;'>$error</p>"; ?>

    <form method="post" action="">
        <label>Username:</label>
        <input type="text" name="username" required><br><br>

        <label>Password:</label>
        <input type="password" name="password" required><br><br>

        <input type="submit" value="Login">
    </form>
<?php endif; ?>
</body>
</html>

HOW IT WORKS:
Login Form â†’ User enters username & password.
If correct (admin / 12345), session variable $_SESSION['admin'] is set.
Admin Dashboard is displayed when session is active.
Logout Link clears session and returns to login form.
